EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring visible shield numbers and rank designations
EventItemMatterName: Requiring visible shield numbers and rank designations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Criminal Justice
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to entrepreneurship training for formerly incarcerated persons
EventItemMatterName: Entrepreneurship training for formerly incarcerated persons.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to provide national funding for the Cure Violence program.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to provide national funding for the Cure Violence program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to authorize adoption by resolution of an interest rate for nonpayment of taxes on real property with an assessed value over two hundred fifty thousand dollars in fiscal year 2021 for certain property owners adversely affected by COVID-19
EventItemMatterName: Authorize adoption by resolution of an interest rate for nonpayment of taxes on real property with an assessed value over two hundred fifty thousand dollars in FY'21 for certain property owners adversely affected by COVID-19.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating a pilot program to test sewage for SARS-CoV-2
EventItemMatterName: Creating a pilot program to test sewage for SARS-CoV-2.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Emergency Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to requiring the emergency management department to report on its response to COVID-19 and the expiration and repeal thereof
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the emergency management department to report on its response to COVID-19 and the expiration and repeal thereof.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to requiring the department of cultural affairs to publish information on COVID-19 reopening plans and resources for art and cultural institutions in New York city
EventItemMatterName: COVID-19 reopening plans and resources for art and cultural institutions in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Disabilities and Addiction
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to providing mental health counseling to healthcare professionals who provided healthcare services during the COVID-19 pandemic, and providing for the expiration and repeal of such requirement
EventItemMatterName: Providing mental health counseling to healthcare professionals who provided healthcare services during the COVID-19 pandemic, and providing for the expiration and repeal of such requirement.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to suspending the schedule change premium when a state of emergency modifies fast food restaurant operations
EventItemMatterName: Suspending the schedule change premium when a state of emergency modifies fast food restaurant operations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and Governor to sign, A.10226-B/S.8211-A, requiring certain perils be covered under business interruption insurance during the COVID-19 pandemic.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring certain perils be covered under business interruption insurance during the COVID-19 pandemic. (A.10226-B/S.8211-A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to report on the number of cases of communicable disease during a state of emergency
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to report on the number of cases of communicable disease during a state of emergency.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation that creates statewide guidelines on closing schools during a biological crisis.
EventItemMatterName: Creates statewide guidelines on closing schools during a biological crisis.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to suspending demolition permits for properties under consideration for landmark or historic district designation
EventItemMatterName: Suspending demolition permits for properties under consideration for landmark or historic district designation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of transportation to conduct an annual study on bicycle activity
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the dept of transportation to conduct an annual study on bicycle activity.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to override Governor Andrew Cuomos veto of S6427A/A8060A, legislation relating to the standards of proof for unfounded and indicated reports of abuse or maltreatment and the admissibility of reports of child abuse and maltreatment.
EventItemMatterName: Relating to the standards of proof for unfounded and indicated reports of abuse or maltreatment and the admissibility of reports of child abuse and maltreatment. (S6427A/A8060A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs and Business Licensing
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to requiring the department of consumer affairs to study access to financial services
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the dept of consumer affairs to study access to financial services.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution opposing the U.S. Department of Homeland Securitys proposed increases to filing fees for immigration status adjustments, including but not limited to, Citizenship, Permanent Legal Residence, Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals, Asylum, and Temporary Protected Status and urging the federal government not to move forward with its adoption.
EventItemMatterName: Opposing the U.S. Department of Homeland Securitys proposed increases to filing fees for immigration status adjustments.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution expressing a loss of confidence in Mayor de Blasio and calling upon the Governor of the State of New York to bring charges to effectuate the removal of the Mayor for failing to protect the safety and promote the general welfare of the public, in accordance with section 33 of the Public Officers Law and section 9 of the Charter.
EventItemMatterName: Expressing a loss of confidence in Mayor de Blasio and calling upon the Governor of the State of New York to bring charges to effectuate the removal of the Mayor

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Criminal Justice
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to pass, and the President to sign, the Emergency Community Supervision Act (S 3579/ HR 6400), which would require the Bureau of Prisons to immediately release vulnerable individuals to home confinement or other community supervision outside of prison to stop the spread of COVID-19.
EventItemMatterName: Emergency Community Supervision Act (S 3579/ HR 6400)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Criminal Justice
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.7658A/S.6276, in relation to providing telephone calls to persons incarcerated in state correctional facilities at no cost.
EventItemMatterName: Providing telephone calls to persons incarcerated in state correctional facilities at no cost. (A.7658A/S.6276)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to giving qualified entities a first opportunity to purchase and an opportunity to submit an offer to purchase certain residential buildings when offered for sale
EventItemMatterName: Giving qualified entities a first opportunity to purchase and an opportunity to submit an offer to purchase certain residential buildings when offered for sale.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring booking services to report short-term housing rental transactions
EventItemMatterName: Requiring booking services to report short-term housing rental transactions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass, and the President to sign, the Eric Garner Excessive Use of Force Prevention Act of 2019 (H.R. 4408), which would prohibit police chokeholds and other tactics that result in asphyxiation.
EventItemMatterName: Eric Garner Excessive Use of Force Prevention Act of 2019 (H.R. 4408)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the establishment of a COVID-19 economic recovery task force
EventItemMatterName: Establishment of a COVID-19 economic recovery task force.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women and Gender Equity
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to a public information and outreach campaign on domestic violence during the COVID-19 emergency, and the repeal thereof
EventItemMatterName: Public information and outreach campaign on domestic violence during the COVID-19 emergency, and the repeal thereof.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Oversight and Investigations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to establishing a special inspector within the department of investigation to review contracts that were entered into in response to the 2019 novel coronavirus, and providing for the repeal of such provision upon the expiration thereof
EventItemMatterName: Establishing a special inspector within the DOI to review contracts that were entered into in response to the 2019 novel coronavirus, and providing for the repeal of such provision upon the expiration thereof.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution expressing a loss of confidence in Mayor Bill de Blasio and calling upon the Governor of the State of New York to bring charges to effectuate the removal of the Mayor for failing to maintain public order and safety during this period of persistent social unrest, in accordance with section 33 of the Public Officers Law and section 9 of the Charter.
EventItemMatterName: Expressing a loss of confidence in Mayor Bill de Blasio and calling upon the Governor of the State of New York to bring charges to effectuate the removal of the Mayor.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to authorize adoption by resolution of an interest rate for nonpayment of taxes on real property with an assessed value of two-hundred and fifty thousand dollars or less in fiscal year 2021 for property owners adversely affected by COVID-19
EventItemMatterName: Deferral of property tax liability on real property with an assessed value of two hundred fifty thousand dollars or less owned by certain property owners impacted by COVID-19.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to guidelines for cleaning and disinfecting multiple dwellings
EventItemMatterName: Guidelines for cleaning and disinfecting multiple dwellings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Economic Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.10430/S.8184-A, which would establish tiers of essential employees during a state of emergency.
EventItemMatterName: Establish tiers of essential employees during a state of emergency. (A.10430/S.8184-A)
